inn1.comm: Right on money. Full and swinging in, Hinds restricts his front movement across and jabs the ball away.
And again. Lands on a length, on the middle, and swings in to rap Hinds on the pads. He falls over while attempting to work it to the on side.
And there you again. Almost on the blockhole, swinging in late, jabbed away.
banged in short and it rises shoulder high outside the off stump, Hinds drops his wrists to get his bat away from the line and lets it go through
Hinds decides to go for a drive outside off. Too much bottom hand in that and the ball rolls over to the on side.
wide called but worth the effort by Lee. It was banged in short and disconcerted Hinds no end. He ducked and also then flinched and threw his bat out at it.
length delivery on the off, pushed to widish mid-off and the first run off the bat.
swinging outside off, left alone
again in the channel outside off, Hinds withdraws his bat away from the line
well outside the off stump, almost a wide, Hinds had nothing to do with it.
outside off stump, swinging away, left alone
again slanted away, starts outside off and veers further away, left alone
lovely outswinger that has Hinds groping forward and leaves him at the last minute. Most of the balls were well outside off in this over but not this one.
full and swinging a bit, pushed to square-leg
length delivery on the middle, Gayle leans forward to defend it away
hit the deck short of length and it climbs up. Gayle adjusts, almost gets squared-up, to push it to point
pushed across Gayle who lets it go through to Gilchrist.
Swung down the leg side. Fullish delivery that swung early in its trajectory.
on the legs, full in length, Gayle brings his bat down in front of his pad, makes sure that the full face is on offer and it rolls towards mid-off
just outside off, inviting a poke but Hinds resists.
whack! Gayle is away. Short and wide and murdered over point
just outside off stump and Hinds has a careful look at it and lets it go through to 'keeper
Got him! Hinds couldn't resist a poke this time and ends up edging straight to Ponting at second slip. A neat outswinger that drew Hinds forward before leaving him.
Bracken gets it to bend back in from a length on the middle and leg and SMith is hit on the thigh pad.
much fuller and just outside off. Swings in a bit and Smith gets a inside edge as he lunges forward.
slanted away and Gayle gets a outside edge that takes the ball to McGrath at thirdman
length delivery on the middle, Smith gets behind the line to push it away down the track. Full face of the blade on offer. Wonder whether he can resist a flashy shot.
And he is beaten outside off. Not a flashy shot but he goes hard at a length delivery outside off, ends up pushing inside the line
came in a touch after landing on a length just outside off stump and punched to mid-on
gets behind the line to a fullish delivery around the off stump and pushes it to the off side
And there he goes. Thumped down the ground. Overpitched outside off and he jumps at it to drill it past mid-off
tip and run. Gayle pushes a fullish delivery towards mid-off and runs with the stroke.
slanted across Smith who ....  lets it go.
moves towards a ball that landed on a length around the off and middle and steers it to backward point where Michael Clarke makes the stop
lovely drive through covers.  He leant into that drive and just timed it. Caressed it softly. No violence.
on the middle and leg, Smith gets behind the line to dead-bat it away. The defensive technique looks pretty good so  far
again the dead-bat is pushed out, full face of the blade comes into play.
great shot! Overpitched allright but still had to put away and he did it in style. Just a firm push and it raced down the ground.
the across the line shot is out now...  A length delivery around the off stump is tapped to widish mid-on
oh what a tame dismissal. Flicked straight to square-leg.  Length delivery on the legs and he couldn't keep his shot down.
Sarwan starts off with a brisk drive past the bowler. He moved towards the ball smartly and went through the line.
And now he carves a short of length delivery outside off past point. He hopped onto his back foot and produced a horizontal stroke. It was there to be hit and he obliged.
Take that! Gayle now joins in the counterattack. He moved back and across, even before release and creamed a length delivery right over the umpire's head!
almost dragged on. No room to cut - it was a length delivery coming in a touch, but Gayle tries nevertheless and gets an inside edge
and now the forward defensive is out.
attempted yorker turns into low full-toss, pushed back down the track
leans forward to a full-length delivery and pushes it to mid-off
Doesn't happen often but Gayle misses out on a boundary. Overpitched outside off and he punched firmly but straight to mid-off.
short of length outside off, steered to thirdman
full and on the leg and middle, turned to midwicket. One slip in place for Gayle.
length delivery on the off stump, punched off the back foot to mid-on. Almost pulled to mid-on.
No second slip for Gayle as I said and Australia pay for it. McGrath squares-up Gayle and produces a edge and it flies through the gap.
Gayle tries to counterattack, goes for a pull but drags it down to backward square-leg
pushes a length delivery to off side, wants a run but Gayle sends him back quickly...
attempted yorker ends as a low full-toss, driven down to Watson at mid-on
angled away, Sarwan gets across and pushes it to off side
slanted outside off, left alone
length delivery that slanted away, steered to point
pushed across Sarwan who lets it go through
tight over comes to an end. Another length delivery that lands around off and middle, Sarwan dead-bats it away to the off side.
full and on the legs, flicked away to deep midwicket
Just outside off, on a length, punched to Clarker at point
fuller and on the middle, Sarwan works his wrists over time and turns it to Hogg at square-leg
kicks up a bit from length, just outside off, pushed to cover
fullish outside off, steered to Clarke at point
again full and outside off, this time Sarwan ekes out a single by running it down to thirdman.
right on target first up. On the stumps and pushed back down the track
almost a mix-up. Sarwan mis-times a push and it rolls towards mid-on. Sarwan wants a run, Gayle resists before agreeing but by then Sarwan changes his mind
fullish on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
outside off and Sarwan gets on top of the bounce and cuts it to right of thirdman

Gayle falls. He was pretty conservative for most of his stay today and perished trying to get a single. It was a length delivery that was slanted away and Gayle opened the face of his bat in an attempt to run it down to third man but sent it straight into the gloves of Gilchrist.
Morton who had a 31-ball duck against Australia last time they played starts off with a boundary.  Overpitched outside off stump and he drills it down the ground.

length delivery on the off that straightens squares up Sarwan. he has always had a problem against this delivery. Gets squared-up, expecting the ball to come in with the angle. Technical deficiency there.
whizzes through in the channel outside off, left alone
just outside off, on a length, steered past gully
McGrath goes up in appeal for lbw after beating a forward prod. But the point of impact was outside the off stump.
length delivery outside off, punched to cover
bouncer sails well over Sarwan's head.
hit the deck short of length and outside off, Sarwan backs away to cut but can't beat the point fielder
slower one on the off stump line, Sarwan leans forward at the last minute and pushes it away to the off side
yorker on the middle and leg, jabbed away to the on side
short and wide, Sarwan stands over it, comes down hard and late and cuts that in the gap at gully for four
a slower half volley outside the off stump, he likes them there does Sarwan, frees the arms and cracks that between cover and point for another boundary
tosses this up outside off, he gets forward and drives to McGrath at mid-off and calls for the run
tossed up again, driven hard to McGrath, no chance of a run this time
flatter on middle stump, worked to the left of Bracken at leg gully for one
full outside off, pushed into the covers
well flighted outside off stump, forward in defense goes the batsman

he's got him this time! Tossed up on off, the one that goes straight on, Sarwan doesnt pick  and goes back lazily, gets struck in front of middle and leg, thats out mate, says the umpire, Clarke strikes in his first over
Just outside off, pushed to point
much fuller and on the off stump line, pushed to off side
short of length outside off, punched to point
outside edge to thirdman gets Lara on strike. Huge cheers go around the arena
inside edge on to the pads. A length delivery on the leg and middle and Lara tries  to work it to on side.
gets squared-up a bit by a length delivery slanting away but manages to push it to mid-on
just outside off,  Lara goes back and across to push it to Ponting at point
length delivery outside off, Morton goes for a drive on-the-up but mistimes it and it rolls over to right of mid-off
pushed across Lara, outside the off stump, left alone
banged in short but it doesn't bounce much . Lara sways away

pushed across L:ara who steers it to right of Clarke at point who moves smartly to his left and throws it at the non -strikers end where Morton just about manages to scamper back int o the crease. The throw missed the sticks, even if it had hit, Mroton would have been home
full-toss, Lara goes for a drive but gets a inside edge and they rush across for a quick single
fullish delivery on the off and middle, pushed back down the track. Gilchris appeals as he thinks it hit the pad first
ful and fast, square-driven to backward point
again overpitched outside off, driven powerfully to cover where Symonds makes a good tumbling stop
slips down the leg side and Lara tries to paddle it away - it was pretty short in langth - but doesn't connect
The whiplash square drive is out. It was short of length, outside off and Lara cracks it off the back foot but once again Symonds makea diving stop.
tip and run. Lara gets off the strike
Lovely punch-drive past point. Short of length outside off, and Morton goes onto his back foot and forces it through the off side ring. Symonds gives the chase but ...
leans forward to a fullish delivery outside off and pushes it to cover
slower ball, 129.kmoh delivery. Lara picks it slightly late and lunges forward at the last minte to steer it to point
on the off, length delivery, Lara gets his bat in front of his pad and pushes it to the off side
pushed across Lara, well outside the off stump, Lara goes back and across towards the ball and chops it down to thirdman
banged in short and it catches Morton by surprise. He takes his bottom-hand out of the bat-handle and jabs at it.
another one banged in short and ends up outside leg stump, pulled down to fine-leg
almost dragged back onto the stumps. Short of length delivery on the off stump, comes in slowly off the pitch and Mroton is through his shot - a backfoot punch- and gets an inside edge
this time punched perfectly to left of mid-on and Lara will face McGrath now
McGrath greets him with a bouncer, Lara hops up first and then ducks under. Not the fastest route to take if you want to go down
fullish on the off stump, pushed to cover point
on the legs, tucked to right of square-leg where Ponting swoops on the ball and has a shy at the non-striker's end
overpitched on the stumps, driven to long-on
from round the stumps,. fullish on the stumps, turned to midwicket
outside off, turning away, left alone
similar ball but this time Lara reaches out to late cut to shrot thirdman
floated on the off, defended away off the front foot
full and just outside off, Morton lets it come to him, bends his right knee and steers it to point.
slapped past mid-off! It was slightly short of length but well outside the off stump and he executed a forehand down the line
on the off stump, just short of driveable length and Morton leans forward to push it to on side.
on the middle and leg, coming in a touch and Morton flicks it away with the angle past suare-leg
Lara leans forward to a full delivery on the middle that leaves him slightly and gets a outside edge as he pushes at it. The ball rolls to point
pushed flat and straight , comes in with the angle, tickled aroudn the corner
floated up on the middle, flicked with the turn, Clarke at midwicket misfields
Clarke again but makes the stop this time.
on the middle and leg, driven to long-on
turns away after landing on the off stump, steered to short thirdman
Lara gets a four without too much risk. He is stil trying to get his eye in. Sweeps from the stumps, and bisects teh fielders at the deep
pushed back down the track
turns with a bit of bounce outside off, Lara cuts it late to short thirdman
flighted delivery on the middle and leg, driven down the ground to long-on
beaten by a peach of a delivery. It landed outside off and ripped through the bat and pad gap as Morton pushes at it. Didn't think it would spin in that sharply
tossed up on off, invites the drive back to the bowler
flighted outside off stump, stands and drives into the covers
flighted outside off again, gets forward and drives past Clarke at mid-off
again he tosses it up, again its driven past Clarke
flighted on off, worked to midwicket
a fraction flatter and shorter, checks his shot to point
flatter on off stump, turned to square leg who moves in quickly
full, driven into the covers
quicker and spinning into him, goes back and works to leg
pitches on the stumps and spins leg side, wide called
lands outside leg stump and its swept along the ground to fine leg
flatter on off stump, pushed to Clarke at point this time
full on off, defended
short outside off, goes to cut but misses
outside off, defended
spinning outside off stump, comes forward and works to square leg
pitches on middle and leg, goes to flick and gets that just off the bat, around the corner speeds the ball and it carries on to the fine leg fence, not a bad shot at all
lands on off and spins away, Lara all over it and smothers the spin
slower and looping into off stump, Lara drops the hands and runs that to backward point
short and spinning away, Lara stands up and cracks that past point to the cover sweeper
short again but cut to Clarke at point
pitches outside leg this time, Lara easily sweeps that down to fine leg, all along the ground, nicely played
very wide outside off stump, Lara' eyes light up and he walks across the stumps and cuts that hard past Clarke and the ball speeds away for four, good shot No.2 of that over
tossed up short outside off stump, he goes back and dabs that past Lee at gully and they steal more easy runs
flatter on the stumps, pushed to mid-off, 50 partnerships up
fullish outside off, pushed to backward point and they steal a run
flatter on off stump, worked to mid-on
tossed up on off stump, Morton again looks to work that to the on side
tossed up again, this time he sensibly drives that to mid-off instead, easy run
short outside off stump, stays a tad low but Morton dabs that towards point for a run
slower and fuller outside off, Lara negotiates that to backward point
moves onto middle and leg, Lara hops and defends to midwicket
fuller on off stump, Lara hops, checks his shot to make sure it stays low, and drives between the stumps and Morton down to long-on
short of a good length outside off stump, Morton punches off the back foot to mid-off
angled into him from outside off stump, Lara stands and steers that past Clarke at backward point
flat outside off stump, punched back to the bowler
flatter on middle and leg, Morton steps forward and adjusts his flick through midwicket, Hogg down on the ropes moves quickly and saves a four just in time, that was close
a fraction short and Lara flashes that hard to backward point
full toss on middle and off, eased into the mid-off region for one
flat on the stumps, Morton whips that past square leg for a brace
gives it a little air outside off stump, Morton comes forward and defends
full outside off stump, Lara likes that and flashes the square drive on bended knee past point, what'd he have to drink a minute ago?
thats the offcutter, slow and full but Lara mistimes the checked drive and gets an inside edge

dropped! Full outside off, Morton has an almighty swing at that, mistimes it high over mid-off and cover, Ponting looks at it and runs back, does well to judge it going back but doesnt hold onto it cleanly, in and out goes the ball, Morton gets a life
full outside off stump, pushed into the covers for a quick run
full outside off and moving away, Morton drives one-handed and gets a thick edge past where slip would have been and the ball runs down to the third man
slow and short outside off stump, Morton taps that back to him
slower ball again, Morton tries to defend but doesnt time it well, plays that awkwardly and the ball rolls to the on side
short and he pulls that hard to Ponting at short mid-off who fields and immediately fires in a throw to the stumps
full outside off stump, driven hard back to Watson
short of a good length outside off stump, checked drive back to Watson again
tossed up on the stumps, swept past square leg for one
short outside off stump, pulled down to mid-off for a single, thats the 100-run stand&
full on the stumps, flicked to midwicket for one, thats Lara's 61st ODI half-century, well played sir
quick and in the blockhole, timings bad for Morton who's bat comes down late, but dug out nevertheless
short and wide, steered to Clarke at backward point who has a shy at the bowler's end and gives away a run courtesy an overthrow
full, attempted yorker, Lara digs that out to Symonds at mid-off
good length ball that comes into him, he adjusts his shot and defends back to Lee
tossed up outside off stump, Morton onto the front foot and pushes to cover, calls for the run
sees Lara coming down, drops it short, Lara caught in a tangle, ball off the pads to the onside
varies the pace, a tad quicker, Lara tries a cheeky glance but misses
quicker on off, pushed into the covers for one
flatter on the stumps, thumped away to mid-on
swept from middle and leg down to fine leg for one, singles still ticking away here
maximum from Lara! Flicked off the pads ever so sweetly, ball sails high over deep square leg for six, uff!!
full again but its worked to midwicket this time
short outside off stump, Morton latches onto that and thumps the pull past square leg for four, beautifully played, timed it very well this time
short outside off and a tad slower, crunches the drive to cover and sets off for a sharp run, beats Clarke's throw but just
full outside off, guided to point
full again, this time its driven to mid-off for a single
tosses this up, its a full toss on leg stump but Lara cant get onto it, ends up pulling down to fine leg for just one
tossed up on off, worked to Symonds at midwicket for one
another full toss one leg stump, Lara can only sweep down to wide fine leg for one
tossed up outside off, Morton comes forward and mistimes the drive, ends up chipping that over Clarke but the ball lands safely in no-mans land between long-off and long-on
swept from middle and off around the corner for one
flatter on the stumps, Lara cant put it away and falls over in his attempted flick
short outside off, cut off the backfoot to cover
fraction short, some spin into him as he attempts to glide that down to third man but misses
comes down, Symonds fires that in quicker and the ball sneaks between Morton's leg, Gilchrist doesnt take it and the ball runs away fine, Ponting gives chase
flicked down to McGrath at deep fine leg, they run, but Lara's in some trouble here, seems to have cramped up
sweeps this from middle and off all the way to the backward square leg fence, he'll take fours instead of singles
sweeps again but not as fine, deep midwicket fielder fires in the throw as Lara hobbles down the other end
and he's welcomed with a fine smack down over his head for four to long-off, what a smash!

he's gone this time! Dropped in a fraction shorter and Lara ltries to latch onto it and smack it over the off side but can only find Symonds at short extra cover, Lara was struggling with the cramp anyways, but what a fine innings from him
middle and off, tucked to Symonds
wuff! Full outside off, Baugh frees the arms and smashes that over the offside, one bounce and into the ropes
slower yorker outside off stump, squeezed down towards gully for one
full attempted yorker again, well kept out by Morton
short and spinning in, Baugh thinks it'll be wide and leaves it
short again, this time he cuts that past point and gully for one
fired into leg stump, well worked to midwicket for one
short again, cut to gully for one more
tossed up slower outside off stump, Morton comes forward and is struck outside the line
right in the blockhole and its defended back to Symonds
in the blockhole, well bowled champ, Baugh can only push back to McGrath
full again outside off stump, Baugh improvises with the cheeky paddle around the corner but misses it, trying the dougie marillier, eh?
full again outside off, he makes room and tries to dab it way, manages to just get bat onto it and squeeze it down to third man
shorter on middle and off, stands and thumps that down to long-on
theres that blockhole warmer again, can only push back to McGrath
full again, this time Morton times it well and hammers that over McGrath, who somehow manages to duck out of the way, ball screams into the long-off fence, firm blow that!
yup, theres the spinners and cutters, full and slow on the stumps, worked to square leg
full and its smashes right between Bracken's legs and like a rocket to Symonds a t long-off, well fielded down there
full and moving into leg stump, Baugh makes so much room and flashes a drive, ball is collected by Gilchrist who appeals, but for what?
slow ball, lapped around the corner to leg gully
in the blockhole, well dug out by Morton into the covers
attempted yorker becomes a low full toss on middle and leg, driven to mid-on
full on off stump, driven down to Symonds at long-on
short on off stump, Baugh ambitiously tries to pull but mistimes that to mid-on
huge, huge! In the zone outside off stump, Morton slams that with a lovely heave and sends that rows back over long-on, what a hit! Treat to watch!
fires in the yorker this time, well dug out to mid-on
full outside off, Baugh goes down and square drives that in the air over gully, one bounce down to Lee at third man
attempted yorker, smashed down to long-on for one, thats the end of McGrath tonight
slow full toss, struck past mid-on to Clarke down on the fence
slower, Baugh looks for the big shot, tries to pull from outside leg but mistimes back to Bracken
laps this from off stump to the man at backward square leg for one
hammered back hard to Bracken who cant hold onto it, ball rolls out of his hands to mid-off for one
gone! In the zone outside off stump, Baugh goes down and tries to hammer that over the offside cordon but can only find Ponting at wide mid-off who holds onto it, ball was travelling at some speed
full toss on middle and leg, can only hit that into the midwicket region for one

inn2.comm: starts off with a wide down the leg side.
length delivery on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
But he spears it in  on the legs, clipped neatly past square-leg.
Jaffa! It landed on a length around the off stump and moved away sharply and late, beats Gilchrist all hands up.
fuller and Gilchrist tries to pounce on it with a drive down the ground but the bat-handle turns in his hands and the ball rolls towards mid-on

Close shave there. The ball seamed in with the angle and went through Gilchrist who wanted to cut. It rapped him high on the back foot before bounding off to left of Baugh who deflects it away. Lovely delivery.
banged in short and Gilchrist quickly swivels to pull it over midwicket. He didn't hit it off the middle but still had the legs to carry past the ropes.
That one hurried Gilchrist. It hastened after pitching on a length, Gilchrist tried to jab it away, got an inside edge on to his pads
full and on the leg and middle, flicked away past square-leg
zips in after pitching on a length, around middle, Gilchrist hops back and works it to square-leg.
fullish and on the middle and leg, Gilchrist mistimes his drive to midwicket
full again and on the middle, Gilchrist plays it to mid-off
in the zone outside off, Watson pushes back to defend it away to the off side
Bradshaw draws first blood. It was banged in short and Watson fetches it from outside the off stump and pulls, but ends up lobbing it up towards mid-on where Sarwan comes under the ball.
just outside off and Gilchrist taps it close to the on side and off they go for a run
beat Ponting with the one that came back in after landing on a length around off stump. Ponting lunged forward and got an inside edge on to his pads
this one went away with the angle and Ponting had this one covered, lets it go through to the 'keeper
fullish on the middle, Ponting, who was lunging forward, gets his left leg off the line quickly and drives straight. It crashes into the sticks at the other end.
hastens after pitching from a length and kicks up as well. Gilchrist shapes to pull but is beaten for pace
full and on the middle, Ponting stays back and deflects it behind square-leg
tip and run. It was on a length, around the off stump line, Gilchrist pushed it towards extra cover and they rushed across for a quick single
90.05 mph delivery that kicked up from a length and went past Ponting before he could get his bat across for a tickle down the leg side.

crash... inside-edge on to the stumps. 140.04 kmph delivery that landed on a length  outside the off stump and held its line, Ponting pushed back and hung his bat out at it - wanted to force it through the off side field , the bat came down in angle and all he got was a inside edge.
fast and on a length, outside the off stump, kicks up chest high outside off stump, Martyn steers it to point
much fuller and straighter, Martyn gets his bat behind it to push it towards mid-off
on the leg and middle, going down with the angle, turned past square-leg
beaten outside off! Martyn hangs his bat out to a length delivery angled across.
tip and run. close one. Martyn leant forward to a fullish delivery on the off, pushed it towards mid-off and ran with the stroke. Morton swooped in and underarmed a throw, missed.
length delivery on the middle, Gilchrist tried to work it to on side, got an outside edge that took the ball to thirdman
Martyn breaks free with a lovely clip in front of square-leg. It was on the legs, knee high, flicked well.
slips down the leg side.
gets right this time, on the off stump, Martyn pushes it towards mid-off
pushed to extra cover.
fuller and on the leg and middle, swung in a touch, Gilchrist, who usually doesn't get his front leg across, waits for the swing to play out before clipping it past square-leg
144.2kmph delivery, on the pads, Martyn fails to flick it away cleanly
142.2kmph delivery on the middle, full in length, Gilchrist pushes it towards mid-off and runs with the stroke.
speared in full on the middle and leg, pushed to mid-on
just short of driveable length, on the off stump line, Gilchrist nudges it down the track
length delivery that comes in with the angle to evade a flick shot and hits the thigh pad
swing and a miss. Gilchrist tries to force a off drive on the up but ends up playing outside the line
down the leg side. 29 for 2. four wides and two leg byes so far.
almost popped it to mid-off. A bit early into his push drive and it goes in the air and  bounces well in front of Sarwan.
length delivery on the off, Gilchrist shuffles a bit and is cramped for room, just jabs it close to him.
bit shorter and Gilchrist is quick to work his wrists to tickle it around the corner. They run hard and will get two
pings the length, just outside off, punched off the front foot to covers.
much fuller and just outside the off stump, Martyn hangs his bat out to push it to cover point.
chinese cut! Martyn chased a delivery outside the off stump, got an inside edge that takes the ball past the stumps and past the short fine-leg man
West Indies are keeping Australia on thier toes. A fierce clip off the legs almost got past short midwicket but Samuels dives to make the stop.
fine-leg up and Taylor sprays on to the legs, nicely clipped away
ouch. Martyn hit flush on the helmet. Banged in short and it reared up, Martyn seemed to have lost sight off the ball and just ducked at the last minute but couldn't evade the bumper.
Gilchrist gets an outside edge as he tries to drill a fullish delivery down the ground and the ball rolls over to point
leans forward to dead-bat a length delivery just outside the off stump
Bradshaw keeps it right up. On the middle and Gilchrist tries to drive past mid-on but hits straight to him.
taps a ball to left of Gayle at short midwicket and they pinch a run
draws Martyn forward with a delivery just short of driveable length, around the off stump.. Martyn hangs his bat out and pushes it to mid-off
slightly slower this time and outside off, Martyn adjusts at the last minute to push it away towards cover point
spears one full outside the off stump, Gilchrist squaredrives it to Dwayne Smith at point
length delivery on the off stump line, Gilchrist goes back and pushes it back down the track
slanted across Gilchrist who stays back to push it left of cover and Bravo fails to make a clean stop
fullish on the off stump, hint of late in swing, Martyn pushes it to mid-on.
Martyn fails to put away a delivery on the legs. He clips it but straight to square-leg
on the middle and leg, worked to midwicket
out comes Martyn's bat, ahead of his body to push a length delivery to short cover
much fuller and outside off stump, Martyn square-drives but can't beat Bravo at point
Hinds misfields at mid-off and turns a dot ball into two.

Bradshaw strikes! A deep point, a backward point and gully were in place. Bradshaw hurled one full and well outside off, Martyn went after it but couldn't keep it down. It flew flat and low and was nose-landing before Bravo, at point,  bent low in front of him to take the catch.
down the leg side. It would have been a wide if it wan't called a no-ball.
angled across Symonds who shoulders his arms
Lovely flick, a nice pick-up shot over square-leg. It was fullish on the legs and Gilchrist gets into the act.
137.9 kmph delivery on the middle and off, pushed to mid-off
on the legs and Taylor was lucky to get away with that. Glanced straight to short fine-leg
attempted yorker, almost on the blockhole, dug away to the off side
Gayle, standing at silly midoff, comes into play as Gilchrist pushes one straight at him. All along the ground though.
Another pick-up shot off the legs. Gilchrist got his wrists working over time and just flicked it high behind square-leg.
angled across Symonds who steers it to point
length delivery on the middle, Symonds tries to work it to on side, bat coming across in a angle, and the ball rolls over the on side
fuller and just outside off, pushed to cover
leans forward to get across to a delivery outside the off stump to push it to extra cover
Symonds hammers a overpitched delivery but hits straight to mid-off
another powerful shot, this time a square-drive to left of point
slightly short of length and Symonds tries to pull it but doesn't connect well.
Huge shout for lbw goes up as Smith gets one to dart back in off a length and Symonds brings his bat across the line and misses. Going down leg may be.
short and Symonds pulls it powerfully to left of longleg. Morton moves smartly to make the stop
again short and swatted away in the gap between midwicket and mid-on.
in the zone outside off stump, left alone.
good length ball outside off stump, Gilchrist defends that off the back foot for cover to collect
moves into him from off stump, tucks that to mid-on
a tad fuller this time on the stumps, works that to mid-on
lands on a sweet spot outside off stump and forces Gilchrist to nibble at it, ball kisses the edge and flies past Baugh who dives to his left but cant get to it, where was the first slip?
drifts onto the pads and its just helped along its way to deep fine leg, touch shot from Gilchrist
lands on a good length, Symonds goes back and pushes to mid-on
drifts to middle and leg, tucked to deep fine leg well where Bravo dives on the ropes and makes contact with the ropes as he does so, four signalled
short and wide, cut hard to backward point on the bounce
short of a good length, Symonds goes back and pushes back to Smith
fuller on middle and leg, chipped to mid-on
slightly short of length outside off, Symonds shapes to cut but his bat comes down in an angle - neither horizontal nor vertical -  and the ball rolls over towards point
pushed flat on the off, played towards cover
flatter on the off stump, Gilchrist comes forward to push it to cover
on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
slips down the leg side
just outside off, Gilchrist tries to steal a single by pushing to right of cover but well fielded
The tight first over comes to an end. On the middle and leg, no pace to work with. worked to midwicket
full and straight, pushed to mid-off
bad delivery and Symonds puts it away. Short and on the leg side, pulled to backward square-leg
much better this time. length delivery that held its line after landing in front of middle, pushed back down the track
another one on the middle and leg, sliding down a bit, Symonds is hit on the pads  as he misses while trying to work it to on side
sprays on the legs, tucked past square-leg
full and on the legs, tucked towards square-leg
turns in from outside off, dead-batted away
driven down the ground to long-off
leans forward to push to cover
tries to force off the back foot but gets an inside edge which takes the ball to bowler
another tight over by Samuels. Full and driven to long-off
slightly short and pulled straight to midwicket
flat and on the off, cut to point
floated up on the middle, pushed back down the track
on a length, around the middle and turns away. Gilchrist goes back to punch it down to long-off
much slower through the air, on the off and middle, dead-batted away

Gayle gets Symonds and breaks out into animated celebrations.!  Symonds comes down the track but is beaten in the flight. The ball threads the bat and pad gap to disturb the furniture. Gayle hops to his left and then to his right, does the routine again before resting on his left side and then circles the air with his right hand -  I have done you in kind of celebration.
slightly short and punched down the ground
turns in from outside off, Clarke lunges forward and gets an inside edge that takes the ball to the on side
again turns in from outside off, again Clarke lunges forward and it spins past the bat, hits the pads and pops up to Baugh. He appeals for a catch but ...
tickled to shortish fine-leg
fullish on the middle, square-driven to deep point.
turns in from outside off, slightly full, and Clarke leans forward to flick it with the spin past square-leg
on the middle, driven to mid-on
Clarke gets a leading edge to a fullish delivery on the middle and leg. Rolls back down the pitch
another full and straight on the middle and leg, Clarke keeps his front foot across and works it past midwicket
in the zone outside off, Clarke lets it go through to the 'keeper
just short of driveable length outside the off stump, again Clarke lunges forward, gets a outside edge that takes the ball to thirdman
Gilchrist drives at a length delivery on the off stump line, the bat-handle rotates in his hands and the ball goes, along the ground, to Bravo
fullish on the off and middle, driven back to the bowler
OMG! Where did that one come from? It pitched a foot outside the off stump, on a length, and not only turned in sharply but kicked up and Baugh recoiled back as it went for his throat
almost chipped to short midwicket. Fullish and just outside off, Clarke tries to work it with the spin and ends up popping it up.
wide outside off, Gilchrist goes for a cut but can't reach it
on the legs, flicked fine
worked to longleg
fullish on the off, driven to striaghtish cover
length delivery on the off stump, Gilchrist tries to force it away but doesn't find pace to work with
Ah! He may not have found pace to force a length delivery but has ample time in pulling a short delivery over backward square-leg. Nonchalant hit.,
this time hit on-the-up, between the bowler and the mid-off
another turns in sharply from outside off, pushed to short leg
tossed up outside off, turns in, Clarke lunges forward to push it away to cover
rank bad ball. short and down the leg side, pulled to fine-leg fence
on a length, outside off, pushed back down the track
leans forward to drive it to long-on
Gilchrist gets a outside edge as he goes for a square-drive to a fullish delivery outside off and the ball rolls past  point
slower ball outside off, Clarke gets forward and tries to drive, mistimes it however
swings into him from off stump, he works that from middle stump past square leg
full again, he falls over in his attempt to flick that through midwicket
that slow again outside off stump, Clarke leans into it and pinches a run in front of Smith's nose at backward point
full outside off stump, he eases into his cover drive but finds a diving mid-off instead
slow full toss, pushed back to the bowler
tossed up, comes onto the front foot and pushes to cover
again, he gets forward and pushes to Sarwan at cover
spins into him from a good length, quicker ball, Clarke defends off the back foot
good top spin on that one, Clarke lunges forward and tries to defend, rapped on the thigh pad
comes forward again, works that to short fine leg
quicker and flatter, Clarke defends again with a straight bat
bad ball, a wide ball down leg, Gilchrist goes for a pull but misses
there's the 50! Good length outside off stump, Gilchrist pokes at that and gets the edge past a diving 'keeper down to third man
good length delivery outside off stump, he checks the drive to the man at extra cover
slower ball, full too, again he checks his stroke and opens the face of the bat, keeps it along the ground to point
short again, he opens the face of the bat and runs that down to wide third man

full and slow as it drifts into middle and leg, Clarke keeps his head over the ball and clips that along the ground through the gap at midwicket, fielder dives in vain and Clarke gets four to his name
slow half volley outside off stump, Clarke walks into his shot and drives to mid-off
spins in from outside off, pushed into the off side
flatter on off stump, Gilchrist forward and smothers the spin
spins into middle and leg, rapped on the pads trying to turn that fine
flatter on the stumps, pushed to mid-off
tossed up, squeezed to wide of point off the front foot
short on middle and leg, Clarke swivels and pulls that to Bravo at backward square leg, he dives but cant get to it cleanly
flatter on the stumps, defended off the back foot
flatter again, goes back and punches to cover
tossed up, turned to midwicket
some turn there, but short and Clarke goes back and chops to gully
flatter on middle and off, goes back and punches to mid-on
lands outside off and spins in, Gilchrist goes back and cuts, gets the edge past a diving slip and races away to the ropes
short and wide, Clarke cracks that down to long-off
short of a good length, defended back to him
lands on off and spins down the pads, wide called
better ball, tossed up and defended
a fraction shorter and its pulled down to deep backward square leg, thats the 50 stand up
short again, Clarke rocks back and pulls over midwicket, fielder on the rope collects
short outside off stump again, Gilchrist this time rocks back and pulls that along the ground to the deep midwicket sweeper, singles ticking alone nicely
short and wide, not able to get that away, only crunches the drive to mid-off
full outside off, defended
tossed up outside off, from wide of the crease, he sweeps and gets rapped on the pads, they appeal but that pitched outside
full again and its defended back to Gayle
drifts to middle and leg and its worked to square leg
short of a good length on off, Clarke goes back and uses the soft hands to push to point and responds to Gilchrist's call
good length on off stump, worked to mid-on
short and wide, Gilchrist slashes hard and watches the ball speed down towards third man where Fidel Edwards slides, slips, and allows the ball to go over the ropes, whoops!
short and wide again, this time he slashes that finer in front of point to Bradshaw in the deep
short of a good length, Clarke hops in the crease and punches to mid-off
short of a length and moves into him, moves across and works that to mid-on
fuller this time and he drives that down to Hinds at long-on
tossed up on off, he comes forward and turns that to midwicket
worked from off stump to midwicket for one
tossed up, Gilchrist defends back to Gayle
flatter and Gilchrist punches that through the off side, Sarwan and Smith get mixed up in their calling and they allow a second run
short and keeps low, defended back to Gayle
tossed up, uses the feet nicely and drives past Gayle down to long-on
shortish, not enough room to cut but Gilchrist does anyways and gets beaten
short and he pulls that along the ground to mid-on
short and angled down leg, he tries to pull but is struck on the thigh pad, they pinch a leg bye
banged in short, Clarke's eyes light up and he pulls that from outside off stump over mid-on for four, good shot
fuller on middle and off, clipped to Samuels at midwicket, who dives and stops, fires in the throw, both batsmen were stranded but Gilchrist makes it back in time
slow yorker outside off stump, Clarke drops the bat and steals a sharp run in front of cover's nose, well done
tossed up on off, defended
dropped short, Clarke rocks back and pulls over midwicket for one down to the sweeper
flighted into middle and off, pushed to mid-on
tossed up on off, Clarke pushes that in front of point and calls for the run
flatter into him, rapped on the pads going for a drive
sweeps this from middle and off down to deep backward square leg
bad ball, drifts down the pads, clipped down to fine leg where Morton dives and fires in a throw
short outside off and moving in, Gilchrist stands and pokes at it, so easily could have taken the outside edge
drifts into him, easily clipped to Bravo at mid-on
good ball, lands on a sweet spot outside off and seams past Clarke's forward prod, some bounce on that one too as it beat the shoulder of the bat, Clarke nods in appreciation
pitches on leg and its clipped around the corner for a single
short again, he opens the face and runs that down to Edwards at third man who fields cleanly this time
tossed up outside off, pushed to point
good ball, tossed up outside off, Clarke smothers the spin with a forward defensive
again Clarke comes forward and defends watchfully, what did Gayle say to him?
and again! Flatter on off stump and Clarke defends with a straight bat
you guessed it! Tossed up outside off stump, and....Clarke DEFENDS!
tell me you all saw this one coming too? Tossed up outside off stump, Clarke goes right back and defends with a straight bat. Some respect this for Gayle...
full and swinging on off stump, Gilchrist drives loosely and gets an inside edge
short and wide, Gilchrist crunches that to mid-off
fuller on the stumps, punched down to long-on for one
good length on the stumps, pushed into the covers...here goes Gayle again, picks the ball up and walks towards Clarke, clapping, smiling and chatting...even Clarke is forced to flash a boyish grin
full outside off stump, Clarke defends to cover
angled wide of off stump, Clarke watches it through to Baugh
full outside off again, Clarke walks into his defense and pushes to mid-off, a good  ball to end Bradshaw's spell.
tossed up on middle and leg, Gilchrist misses his sweep
tossed up on middle and off, Gilchrist sweeps ferociously in the gap at square leg  for four, good shot
pitches on middle and off and straightens, raps the pads as he misses the sweep, not a bad shout that but Koertzen stands motionless
tossed up, pushed to mid-off
keeps low in front of the stumps, worked to midwicket
lands on leg and Gilchrist misses his sweep again
short on middle and off, tucked off the pads to square leg
fullish outside off stump, Gilchrist drives in the air over mid-off for one
flatter, Clarke walks across and tucks that to square leg
flatter outside off stump, Gilchrist sweeps, gets a top edge over Baugh's head and down to the third man fence, lucky shot
flatter and shorter, punched back to Samuels
flatter outside off stump, Gilchrist pushes that into the covers
flat on middle and leg, worked past square leg for a couple, thats the 100-run stand, well batted
tossed up on middle and leg, looks to work fine but gets an edge that rolls to the off side
full outside off, pushed to point

gone! Spins into him from outside off stump, Clarke leans back and runs that towards to Hinds at gully, who picks it up and fires in a good throw to Gayle, Gilchrist is stuck somewhere down the pitch and cant get back in time, Gayle takes the throw and whips off the bails, Gilchrist has to go and boy does Gayle love this! He's whooping it up out there like a school kid after his final examinations! Hah, he says to Clarke!
tossed up outside off, pushed back to Gayle who loses his cool and throws it back but its too high and goes away for overthrows, stupid, stupid move that from him
tossed up, defended
outside off stump, steered to point
flighted outside off stump, he leaves it alone
tossed up, he defends to the offside and calls for the quick run
tossed up on off stump, worked to mid-on

pitches on middle and leg, Clarke delicately uses the pace and glides that around the corner for four, Gayle dives and misfields, the ball runs away and whats this? The umpire signals leg byes? No, no, that was off the bat! Geez....
flatter this time, defended
pitches outside leg stump and Hussey dads that defly and the ball runs away for four
lands outside off stump, steered away towards gully
tossed up on off stump, Clarke drives back to Gayle
tossed up on off, Clarke turns that in front of square leg
spins down the leg stump, wide called
spins into him from outside off stump, steered in front of gully
flatter on off stump, Clarke whips the drive back to Gayle who fields it well
goes back to one that spins into him, turns that square and they set off, Hussey wants the second and a throw comes in wayward, Hussey dives and makes his ground
lands on middle and off, Clarke works that to square leg
spins into him from middle and off, Hussey plays and misses
lands around off stump, he dabs that and wants the run but Clarke sends him back
pitches on leg stump and Hussey tucks that down to fine leg for a brace
tossed up on off stump, worked to mid-on, no run though
lands on middle and off, worked to midwicket
tossed up outside off, left alone
turn and spin, Hussey pokes at it and gets an edge, but it bounces in front of slip
tossed up again, spins away, Hussey misses the cut
tossed up, clipped through midwicket for two

and he strikes with his lethal slower one! Pitches it up super slow, inviting that forward prod, which Clarke does and Bravo just pouches it! And he was already in position moving to his left to take the catch! What a set up from Bravo, incredible!
slower ball outside off stump, a yorker, and Hogg pushes that to cover
right into him again, full and in the zone, Hogg pushes back to Bravo
fullish outside off stump, Hogg backs away and just chips that over mid-off for four, well played, sir
full outside off stump, a very good response from Bravo, Hogg backs away and gets beaten
identical ball, a beauty considering the situation, Hogg again makes room but cant get it away, gets beaten again, hoo hah!
lands this one slowly outside off, he stands and drops the hands and steals a run in front of cover
slower ball in the blockhole, Hogg squeezes that to Gayle at point, he's making room each ball he faces
full outside off stump, he charges and drives that past point to the sweeper in the deep, Taylor bangs into Hussey at the nonstrikers end
short and wide, slow too, stands and hits that along the ground to Gayle at point, a dot ball!

cleaned him up! Fullish delivery, Hussey has an ambitious and ugly swipe across the line - frustration, you'd have to say - misses it all ends up and the ball hits off stump, crucial strike from Taylor, thats the big one West Indies wanted, crowd erupts!

and he's gone first ball! Taylor's a star tonight under the starry skies of Mumbai! Fires in one on a good length on off stump that nips in and catches Lee falling forward, gets rapped in front of middle and leg, every West Indian goes up in appeal, all eyes on Koertzen who takes his time and then ever so slowly raises that left arm...Taylor on fire, Lee departs first ball
full outside off, he makes room and drives to mid-off
full again, Bracken swipes across the line and sets off, Hinds at mid-on fires in a throw that just misses the stumps
full outside off stump, he crashes that past point and they run hard to pick up two
full right on the stumps, Hogg makes room and drives past the gap at cover for one down to Samuels who moves in quickly from the ropes

oh my word, that was close! Theres that slower ball, full outside off, changes the pace and Bracken has a huge slog at it and the ball just misses off stump! Bravo cant believe it as he sits down on the pitch
similar ball, a tad wider, Bracken again gives it the kitchen sink but fails to make contact, crucial dot ball again, we're into the last over, people!

and he gets it, can you believe it?!? History is made at the Brabourne Stadium! Wow, wow, wow! Taylor will never be forgotten here in Mumbai! A full, fast delivery on the stumps, Hogg just walks across, looking to work that around the corner but the man makes zero contact and the ball castles into middle stump, he's gone and West Indies are one away from victory
full outside off, he slogs that do deep square leg
full outside off stump, Bracken slogs and gets an inside edge to leg gully
full on off stump, worked to midwicket
full outside off stump, again he gets an inside edge to leg gully, thats the match for West Indies
full, played to midwicket but its all over here! The West Indies have won by 10 runs, what a remarkable win for them, stunned Australia here
